snippet: A local folk artist tends to Coco, a life-size stuffed ape, on an undeveloped property worth an estimated $8 million in the rapidly developing neighborhood.
abstract: Undeveloped corner lot in rapidly developing area of Williamsburg, Brooklyn, value of which is estimated at over $8 million, has contained nothing but weeds, refuse, old toys and mysterious stuffed gorilla for decades; lot's display of odds and ends is attempt by retiree Carmen Bonilla to carry on legacy of ppoperty's deceased former owner and entertain neighborhood children, but it it unlikely to remain undeveloped for long.
lead_paragraph: A local folk artist tends to Coco, a life-size stuffed ape, on an undeveloped property worth an estimated $8 million in the rapidly developing neighborhood.

headline.main: On Williamsburg Corner, Keeper of a Toy Gorilla, and Old Brooklyn
